.TH "Sdb" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.PP
#Sdb()# #NAME#
.PP
Sdb - connection sequoiadb
.PP
#SYNOPSIS# \f[B]var db = new Sdb([hostname],[svcname])\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]var db = new Sdb([hostname],[svcname],[username],[password])\f[R]
.PP
#CATEGORY#
.PP
Sdb
.PP
#DESCRIPTION#
.PP
Create a Sdb object to connect to the sequoiadb.
.PP
#PARAMETERS#
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]hostname\f[R] ( \f[I]String\f[R]\[uFF0C] \f[I]Required\f[R] )
.RS 2
.PP
Target hostname, default to be \[lq]localhost\[rq].
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]svcname\f[R] ( \f[I]int\f[R]\[uFF0C] \f[I]Required\f[R] )
.RS 2
.PP
Target svcname, default to be 11810.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]username\f[R] ( \f[I]String\f[R])
.RS 2
.PP
If a user name is set when the sequoiadb is installed, it is required, default
to be empty.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]password\f[R] ( \f[I]String\f[R] )
.RS 2
.PP
If a password is set when the sequoiadb is installed, it is required, default to
be empty.
.RE
.PP
#RETURN VALUE#
.PP
On success, return an object of Sdb.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.PP
#ERRORS#
.PP
the exceptions of \f[C]Sdb()\f[R] are as below:
.PP
