.TE
.PP
When error happen, use getLastErrMsg() to get the error message or use
getLastError() to get the error code.
See troubleshooting for more detail.
.PP
#HISTORY#
.PP
since v1.12
.PP
#EXAMPLES#
.IP "1." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the default sequoiadb, hostname default to be
\[lq]localhost\[rq]\[uFF0C]svcname default to be 11810.
.nf
\f[C]
> var db = new Sdb()
\f[R]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the sequoiadb on the specified host, target
hostname is \[lq]sdbserver1\[rq].
.nf
\f[C]
> var db = new Sdb(\[dq]sdbserver1\[dq],11810)
\f[R]
.fi
.RE
.IP "3." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the sequoiadb on the specified host using the
default username and password.
default username and password are empty.
.nf
\f[C]
> var db = new Sdb(\[dq]sdbserver1\[dq],11810,\[dq]\[dq],\[dq]\[dq])
\f[R]
.fi
.RE
.IP "4." 3
Create a Sdb object connection to the sequoiadb on the specified host with a
username and password.
.nf
\f[C]
> var db = new Sdb(\[dq]sdbserver1\[dq],11810,\[dq]sdbadmin\[dq],\[dq]123\[dq])
\f[R]
.fi
.RE
